The [[Bayer designation]] '''Mu Scorpii''' (μ Sco, μ Scorpii) is shared by two [[star system]]s, in the [[constellation]] [[Scorpius]]: * [[Mu1 Scorpii|μ¹ Scorpii]] - a binary star whose primary is named Xamidimura * [[Mu2 Scorpii|μ² Scorpii]] (named Pipirima) They are separated by 0.1° in the sky.
They are separated too into different asterism in [[Chinese astronomy]]. μ¹ Scorpii was a member of asterism 尾 (Wěi), ''Tail'' and μ² Scorpii was the sole star in asterism 神宮 (Shéngōng), ''Changing Room (of the temple)''. Both asterisms are part of the ''[[Tail (Chinese constellation)|Tail]]'' mansion.<ref>{{zh icon}} [http://aeea.nmns.edu.tw/2006/0605/ap060510.html AEEA (Activities of Exhibition and Education in Astronomy) 天文教育資訊網 2006 年 5 月 10 日]</ref>
