'''Trembling aspen''' ({{lang-tr|Titrek Kavak}}) is an old aspen tree in [[Konya Province]], central Turkey. It is a registered [[List of natural monuments of Turkey|natural monument]] of the country.

The trembling aspen is located inside the Yakamanastır Nature Park at [[Bademli, Beyşehir|Bademli]] village in [[Beyşehir]] district of Konya Province. Its distance to Bademli village is {{convert|3|km|mi|abbr=on}} and to Beyşehir town {{convert|8|km|mi|abbr=on}}. It is a quaking aspen (''[[Populus tremula]]''). The tree is {{convert|20|m|ft|abbr=on}} high, has a circumference of {{convert|8|m|ft|abbr=on}} at {{convert|2.50|m|ft|abbr=on}} diameter. Its age is dated to be about 100 years old. [[Offshoot (plant)|Lateral shoot]]s of the old tree are broken by wind.<ref name="os8b"/>

The tree was registered a [[natural monument]] on September 27, 1994. The protected area of the plant covers {{convert|2490|m2|sqft|abbr=on}}.<ref name="tz"/><ref name="mp"/>

